Boating-licence — licensing
===========================

This repository contains two kinds of first-party material, under two different
licences, plus third-party content that keeps its own upstream licence. The
split matters: the tooling is permissively licensed, but the generated study
corpus inherits a share-alike obligation from its Wikipedia-derived parts.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. SOFTWARE / TOOLING  —  MIT License
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
All source code in this repository — the build pipeline (`src/`, `tools/`,
`run.py`), the dependency-free static player (`web/` HTML/CSS/JS), the tests,
and the build scripts — is licensed under the MIT License:

