------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. GENERATED CONTENT  —  CC BY-SA 4.0
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The generated study corpus — the knowledge bases, the source-cited question
banks, and their exports (the JSON bundles, Anki decks, and Moodle GIFT files
produced by the pipeline) — is licensed under Creative Commons
Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0):

    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Why share-alike: part of this corpus is derived from CC BY-SA 4.0 Wikipedia
material (the seamanship/knots, sailing-technique, and meteorology themes).
CC BY-SA's share-alike condition is viral — any work derived from it must carry
the same licence. To keep reuse simple and unambiguous, the entire generated
corpus is offered under CC BY-SA 4.0 rather than tracking the obligation theme
by theme. If you reuse it, you must:

  - attribute "Boating-licence (https://github.com/HugoFara/boating-licence)"
    together with the upstream sources cited on each unit and each question, and
  - license your derivative under CC BY-SA 4.0.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. INGESTED UPSTREAM CONTENT  —  keeps its own licence
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Law and reference material ingested by the pipeline retains its own upstream
licence, recorded as a per-unit and per-question licence note (see
`src/sources.py` and each country module under `src/countries/`):

  - Swiss federal law (ONI, RNL, BSO via Fedlex) ...... public domain
  - French official acts (Légifrance / DILA LEGI) .... Licence Ouverte / Etalab 2.0
  - German federal law (gesetze-im-internet.de) ...... public domain — §5(1) UrhG
  - German ELWIS question catalogues ................. §5(2) UrhG amtliches Werk
                                                        (verbatim, cite www.elwis.de,
                                                        unmodified)
  - COLREG 1972 (US Coast Guard reproduction) ........ public domain — 17 USC §105
  - Wikipedia (knots / sailing / meteorology) ........ CC BY-SA 4.0, attribution
  - MétéoSuisse / cantonal pages ..................... official public-sector,
                                                        reuse with attribution

Material that does not meet the project's reuse bar is never ingested — notably
the Swiss asa exam bank, the French operator QCM banks (La Poste / Dekra / SGS /
Bureau Veritas), the non-free Bodensee-Schifferpatent catalogue, and the CEVNI
(UNECE Resolution No. 24) text. See the per-country documents under `docs/` for
the full reasoning.
